<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Amos on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/</link><description>Recent content in Amos on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Amos 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-1">Amos Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="conversational-yahveh-covenant">Conversational Yahveh Covenant&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The Message of Amos, Shepherd from Tekoa, That He Saw About Israel &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>at &lt;b>the Time of Uzziah, King of Judah, and Jeroboam Ben-Joash, King of Israel, &lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="two-years-before-the-earthquake">Two Years Before the Earthquake&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He said,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      “Yahveh will roar from Zion;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            he’ll thunder from Jerusalem.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      The shepherds’ pastures will dry up;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Amos 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-2">Amos Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh says,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“For three sins of &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Moab &lt;b>and for four,&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="i-wont-hold-back-its-punishment">I won’t hold back its punishment:&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      they burned the king of Edom’s bones into lime.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         2&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;b>I’ll burn the fortresses in &lt;/b>Kerioth;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;i>&lt;span lang=DE style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Moab will die amid turmoil,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span lang=DE style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>war cries, and bugle blasts.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Amos 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-3">Amos Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="witnesses-summoned-against-israel">Witnesses Summoned Against Israel&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Listen to what Yahveh says against you, Israel, against the entire family he brought out of Egypt:&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         2&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Of all the families in the world, only you have me;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            so I’ll punish you for your sins.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         3&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Can two men walk together unless they’ve agreed on their route?&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Amos 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-4">Amos Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="israel-does-not-learn">Israel Does Not Learn&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Listen to this, you cows of Bashan living in Samaria, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      &lt;i>you women
&lt;/i>that oppress the poor and crush the needy, &lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      that tell their husbands, &lt;i>“Bring the wine so we can get drunk!”&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The Lord Yahveh has sworn by his holiness,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;i>“The time’s coming when they’ll take you away with meat hooks,&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Amos 5</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-05/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-05/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-5">Amos Chapter 5&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="yahveh-god-of-hosts-amos-412-13">Yahveh God of Hosts.                                         Amos 4:12-13&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="a-call-to-repentance">A Call to Repentance&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Listen to the dirge I’m chanting for you, Israel:&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         2&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“She’s fallen; &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            virgin Israel won’t get up again.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      She’s abandoned on the ground;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            no one will help get her up.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                           3&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The city that goes out 1,000 strong&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Amos 6</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-06/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-06/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-6">Amos Chapter 6&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>     6&lt;sup>:1&lt;/sup>&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Misfortune awaits those of you at ease in Zion,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  who feel secure in Samaria,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            you notable leaders of that foremost nation&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  that the House of Israel comes to.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         2&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Go over to Calneh and look at what happened there;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  go from there to Hamath the great &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>city&lt;i>;&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Amos 7</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-07/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-07/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-7">Amos Chapter 7&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="a-vision-of-locusts">A Vision of Locusts&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The Lord Yahveh showed me a vision. He formed a locust swarm after the spring crop sprouted and the king had mowed his share. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The swarm had finished eating the vegetation, and I said, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      &lt;b>“Lord Yahveh, please pardon!&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="how-will-joseph-make-it">How will Joseph make it?&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="hes-too-small">He’s too small!”&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh changed his mind.&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Amos 8</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-08/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-08/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-8">Amos Chapter 8&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="israel-will-go-into-exile--amos-710-17">Israel will go into exile.’”                                    Amos 7:10-17&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="a-vision-of-ripe-fruit">A Vision of Ripe Fruit&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The Lord Yahveh showed me a basket of ripe fruit.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“What do you see, Amos?”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“A basket of ripe fruit.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“My people Israel are also ripe—&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>for punishment.&lt;i> I won’t spare them any longer. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The singing at the palace will turn into wailing. There’ll be lots of corpses silently thrown out everywhere.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Amos 9</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-09/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/amos/chapter-09/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="amos-chapter-9">Amos Chapter 9&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="a-vision-of-the-lord-by-the-altar">A Vision of the Lord by the Altar&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I saw Yahveh standing by the altar. He said,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      “Strike the capitals till the thresholds shake;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            shatter them on the people’s heads.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      What’s left, I’ll slay with the sword;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            no fugitive will get away or refugee escape.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         2&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Though they dig down to Sheol,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>